  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a study in adult subjects with complicated urinary tract infection (cUTI) comparing
      treatment with intravenous (IV) coadministered ceftaroline fosamil and NXL104 versus
      treatment with IV doripenem.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
